<h2>Add Questions</h2>

<form name="input" action="questions" method="post">
  <p>You can ask up to 5 questions in your survey.</p>
  <p>This is how the questions will look when you're done:</p>
  <img src="/img/question-screenshot.png">
  <p>The first 4 questions must answerable with simply "Agree" or "Disagree".</p>
  <p>Give each of these questions a title, so you can match it later to the audio you'll be recording, and the question you're asking. </p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <input type="text" name="questions[agree_questions][][short_name]" class="short_name" placeholder="Example: Property Outcome" required>
      <input type="text" name="questions[agree_questions][][question_text]" class="question_text" placeholder="Example: Do you think this property should be demolished?" required>
    </li>
    <% (1..3).to_a.each do |number| %>
      <li>
        <input type="text" name="questions[agree_questions][][short_name]" class="short_name" placeholder="Example: Property Outcome">
        <input type="text" name="questions[agree_questions][][question_text]" class="question_text" placeholder="Example: Do you think this property should be demolished?">
      </li>
    <% end %>
    <li>
      <p>The final question can be open ended.</p>
      <input type="text" name="questions[voice_question_text]" class="question_text" placeholder="Example: What would make this park better?" required>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <input type="submit" value="Next step">
</form>
